OL,3,CTwo million pounds spent on stalled
OL,4,Cresidential centre for women offenders
OL,6,FA women's residential pilot in
OL,7,FSwansea, which would have supported 50
OL,8,Flow-level offenders, has stalled at a
OL,9,Fcost of more than #2million, figures
OL,10,Fobtained by ITV Wales have shown.
OL,12,FThe Swansea Women's Residential Centre
OL,13,Fin Cockett was given the go-ahead last
OL,14,Fyear after a successful planning
OL,15,Fappeal.
OL,17,FThe rehabilitation scheme earmarked
OL,18,Ffor the Trehaford building in the city
OL,19,Fwas due to open in January this year.
OL,20,FHowever, the project has not
OL,21,Fprogressed.
