OL,6,FResidents in Cockett, living opposite
OL,7,Fthe Trehafod building, campaigned
OL,8,Fagainst the women's residential scheme
OL,9,Fbeing placed so close to their homes.
OL,11,FThey made objections during the
OL,12,Fplanning process, saying the site was
OL,13,Funsuitable for women needing
OL,14,Frehabilitation due to its semi-rural
OL,15,Flocation, poor transport links, and a
OL,16,Fpub and school being metres away.
